arts.ttl: Nantes scores late in a 1-0 win against 10-man Rennes as coach Sampaoli sees red
arts.sum: Nantes scored late to beat 10-man Rennes 1-0 in the French league on Sunday and a chaotic finish saw Rennes coach Jorge Sampaoli sent off in stoppage time after a video replay ruled out an equalizer. Defender Christopher Wooh scored from a corner in the fourth minute of stoppage time for Rennes, but after a VAR check referee Mickaël Leleu ruled it out for a handball.
